text.tspan: Please remain home if you have any of the following symptoms:
Cough, runny nose, sneezing, chills, body ache, headache,
sore throat, new loss of taste or smell, fever greater than or equal
to 100.4 F, known close contact with a person who has tested positive
for COVID-19 and has not been symptom free for at least 14 days.
Any child or adult exhibiting these symptoms will be asked
to leave and will not be entitled to a refund.
All guests must wash or sanitize their hands
before entering the play area.
Parents and guardians - not Kids Town staff - are responsible for
children and must remain on site at all times.
Kids Town is not responsible for any lost, damaged or stolen items.
Please keep track of your belongings.
No food or drinks are allowed in the play area.
Please watch your head when entering any of the play structures.
Kids Town has a ZERO bullying policy.
Any child or adult seen bullying or harassing others will be asked
to leave and will not be entitled to a refund.
Children should not climb up onto any Kids Town features
including walls and furniture.
RULES
Children must be respectful of Kids Town toys and property.
Anyone being destructive to the toys or property will be asked
to leave and will not be entitled to a refund.
